"Abstract Downstream liability is an issue that all business managers need to be aware of. While legally complex, the issue is quite simple. If your network is used as the base for a cybercrime in which damage is inflicted on a third party organization, then who is liable? The owner of the originating network or the victim organization? Common sense tells us that liability lies with the owner of the originating network. However, while downstream liability is currently only a concept, it is likely to be tested in court soon."
